They decided to stop a car to carry out the route control. The driver did not follow the instructions, suddenly increased the speed and tried to avoid the control.
The police started the persecution until the car stopped at the edge of the road after a few kilometers. At that moment, the drivers got out of the car to flee to a forest area via a country road.
The police of the city of Ertzaintza finally caught up with one of the two. In the car, an Iveco Daily, the drug traffickers transported 2,178 kilos of hashish, which was confiscated by the police.
The front part of the car was loaded with hashish bundles, which were later directed to the exact laboratory analysis and weighing the bundles to other police stations.
In addition, the officials found that the license plate was `doubled', so that it did not match the license plate indicated in the car papers, which is why there was also an arrest for falsification of official documents.
The police of the city of Ertzaintza continue the investigation to arrest the second suspect, who, as mentioned above, managed to escape, but also to determine the origin of the seized drugs.
28-year-old A. A. J., who was arrested, was taken to a police station for questioning.
Actress Heather Locklear was arrested for driving under the effect of an unknown drug.
The actress Heather Locklear, who is known for the role of Amanda from the series "Melrose Place", was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California, for driving under the effect of an unknown drug.
A witness observed how she tried to get out of her parking space in Montecito in a rather strange way, spokesmen of the California traffic police reported to the magazine 'People'.
The witness explained in detail that Locklear `pushed through the accelerator after 4:30 p.m. and made a lot of noise by trying to move her car backwards or forwards out of the parking space, and as she drove backwards, she grabbed her sunglasses several times'.
A little later, the Witness, who at first had probably not recognized the actress, saw Locklear stopping on a nearby street and getting out of the car.
The witness was the person who notified the emergency service because she was 'afraid of Locklars'.
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting in her car, standing across the street blocking traffic.
'She seemed disoriented,' so the police took her to a special drug and alcohol center to do a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress showed herself cooperative, excessive drinking was excluded from the first moment. 'The first observations of the officials to follow, we believe, that Locklear was under the influence of an unknown drug,' says the speaker.
Locklear was arrested under suspicion of driving under the influence of an indeterminate substance that could not be determined and taken to a local detention centre at around 7:00 p.m.
Two months ago Locklaer was released from the Arizona hospital after treatment, where she was treated for anxiety and depression.
