He asked for bills about the consumptions, in order to be able to later issue invoices based on these templates for the Ministry of Youth and Sports, the Ministry of Social Affairs and Labour, as well as the self-government of Budapest.
The majority of these accounts are said to have been manipulated by István Lados and his accomplice András Ri, who according to our information was responsible for the constitution of the relevant reports.
One of the goals of Lados' "exploratory tour" was a beer pub.
As can be seen from two invoices issued by Hammer and Co in 2003, the catering company is said to have hosted the ninety-member group of the association Biztos Pont Egyesület.
