Like the Central Statistics Office, domestic sales prices rose by 0.1 percent in August 2008 compared to the previous month, and by 12.9 percent compared to August 2007.
Export prices were 1.1 percent higher than in July 2008, and fell by 3.9% compared to the previous year.
Due to domestic and export price changes, production prices were 0.7% higher than in the previous month, and 3.2 percent higher than in 2007.
Domestic sales prices rose only marginally compared to the previous month, i.e. by 0.1 percent.
